### Summary
[[Debian]] package format.

### Example Usage
<pre>
dpkg --status packagename
</pre>

### Putting a package on hold
<pre>
echo packagename hold | dpkg --set-selections
</pre>
"Unhold":
<pre>
echo packagename install | dpkg --set-selections
</pre>

### Package Diversions
<pre>
dpkg-divert --add /bin/sh
</pre>
<pre>
dpkg-divert --remove /bin/sh
</pre>

### Disable Recommends / Recommended Packages
I found this tip useful for /etc/apt/apt.conf.d/70debconf:
<pre>
APT::Install-Recommends "0";
</pre>

### Notes
I found this useful when trying to build [[Midori]]:
<pre>
LD_LIBRARY_PATH=/usr/lib:/usr/local/lib dh_shlibdeps -v --dpkg-shlibdeps-params=--ignore-missing-info
</pre>

